en_223395_0	A majority of the members of the Daayaka Sabawa of the Kelaniya Rajamaha Viharaya voted in favour of the removal of Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe from the post of chairman of the Dayaka Sabha.
en_223395_1	This is when the dayaka sabha convened last afternoon under the patronage of chief Incumbent of the Kelaniya Rajamaha Viharaya Venerable Professor Kollupitiye Mahinda Sangharakkitha Thero.
en_223395_2	Over 100 members had voted in favour of the prime ministers removal from the position of chairman while 7 voted against the proposal.
en_223395_3	Following this it was decided that prime minister Ranil Wickramasinghe would be removed from the position of chairman of the Kelaniya Raja Maha viharaya Dayaka sabha.
en_223395_4	Such a change in chairmanship in the dayaka sabha at the Kelaniya Raja Maha viharayaka is taking place after 35 years.
